machinery /məˈʃiːnərɪ/

1. N-UNCOUNT You can use machinery to refer to machines in general, or machines that are used in a factory or on a farm. 机器; 机械 

例： ...quality tools and machinery. …优质工具和机械。 

2. N-SING The machinery of a government or organization is the system and all the procedures that it uses to deal with things. (政府或组织的) 体制 

例： The machinery of democracy could be created quickly. 民主体制很快就能建立起来。

